  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Organized labor has taken a hand\nin the agitation for the appointment\nof matrons to have charge of the\nwoman prisoners in the city jail.\nAt a meeting Of the Spokane Sec\ntional Central Labor council last\nLight committee of three was\nappointed to confer with the mayor,\nChief of Police Sullivan and the\ncity council and to do what it could\nin behalf of organized labor in Spo-\nkane, toward securing the appoint\nment of three matrons to work in\nshifts of eight hours each in order\nthat the female prisoners will have\nd woman attendant at all times OF\nthe day and night."
